.TH "mlx4_get_module_info" 9 "mlx4_get_module_info" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mlx4_get_module_info \- Read cable module eeprom data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mlx4_get_module_info
.BI "(struct mlx4_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "u8 port "  ","
.BI "u16 offset "  ","
.BI "u16 size "  ","
.BI "u8 *data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
mlx4_dev.
.IP "port" 12
port number.
.IP "offset" 12
byte offset in eeprom to start reading data from.
.IP "size" 12
num of bytes to read.
.IP "data" 12
output buffer to put the requested data into.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Reads cable module eeprom data, puts the outcome data into
data pointer paramer.
Returns num of read bytes on success or a negative error
code.
